<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-02-06T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-02-06T11:00:00-05:00" n="786" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d786">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">837.154/105: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Guggenheim</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-02-06T11:00:00-05:00">February 6, 1930—11
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 12:30 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>20. My telegram number 17, February 5, noon. Investigation enables me to
                            say that the present status of Cuban Government finances would not in my
                            opinion justify our Government in raising objection to the proposed
                            Chase loan.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Guggenheim</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>